<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.248145>
    dc:description "FIGURE 20. Bryopesanser tilbrooki sp. nov.: A, colony on sand grain. B, several autozooids in a hollow of a grain. C, three zooids showing long hollow spines at lateral to distal edges of orifice. D, ovicelled zooid, showing smooth imperforate calcification and raised proximal margin. E, an orifice with seven spines; one of the paired avicularia can be seen at right of the orifice. F, another zooid, showing spines and avicularia. Scale bars: A – C, 0.2 mm; D, F, 0.1 mm; E, 0.05 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/248145/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

